<body background="gif/aaiiback.gif">



<P ALIGN="center">

<A HREF="map/head.map"><IMG SRC="gif/head_about.gif" ALT="AAII logo" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=64 BORDER=0 ISMAP></A>
<H2  ALIGN="center">
<br>
What We've Got</H2>
<hr>
AAII offers a broad array of assistance in learning about investing and finance.  Listed below you will find some help with many of the topics we cover.  Understanding the <A HREF="basics/invbasics.html">Basics </A>will always help you understand the advanced material.  Read more about how to <STRONG>pick mutual funds, stock analysis</STRONG>, and planning for <STRONG>retirement </STRONG> in our index below. <p>

If you are starting to think about retirement planning, which you should be, no matter what your age, read about some <A HREF="finplann/retrmyth.html">Myths of Retiremnent Planning</A>, some <A HREF="finplann/retirinc.html">Sources of Retirement Income</A>, or do you need to know  <A HREF="finplann/rphowsav.html">How Much of your Salary to save?</A><p>

Just want to <STRONG>browse</STRONG> the retirement planning topics?<P>

If yu own mutual funds, maybe you have often wondered 
<A HREF="mutfunds/sellorno.html">to sell or not to sell</A>?  What <A HREF="stocks/growvval.html">Investment style</A> should you take when investing in mutual funds?  AAII has conducted several <STRONG>interviews</STRONG> with mutual fund portfolio managers.  Read about their investment thoughts and styles here in <STRONG>Point of View</STRONG>.<P>

Just want to <STRONG>browse</STRONG> the mutual fund topics?<P>

AAII has compiled a complete investment guide that can help you track down information on <STRONG>Financial Planners, Variable Annuities</STRONG>, or buying <STRONG>Insurance</STRONG>.<P>

Trying to figure out how to pick your stocks?  Here are some guidelines for selecting stocks to <STRONG>start your portfolio</STRONG>.  Want to learn how to 
<A HREF="stocks/fsknowab.html">financial statements</A>?  If you are investing with your Child in mind, read about <STRONG>funding Education</STRONG>, or <A HREF="finplann/kidsmony.html">Teaching Financial Responsibilty</A>.<P>

Click here to see an exhaustive list of investment topics from AAII. <p>

