<H1>Organic Gardening</H1>

<P>
<HR></P>

<P><IMG SRC="carrots.jpg" HEIGHT=99 WIDTH=65></P>

<P><B>Carrots Love Tomatoes - Secrets of Companion Planting</B> <I>Louise
Riotte</I> $9.95 An A to Z compendium of the secrets of companion planting
for successful gardening. This practical book describes plants that help
each other to grow well.</P>

<P><BR>
<IMG SRC="item06.gif" ALT="*" HEIGHT=112 WIDTH=72 ALIGN=BOTTOM> </P>

<P><B>How To Grow More Vegetables</B> <I>John Jeavons</I> $14.95... than
you ever thought possible, in less land than you can imagine. That's the
full title of the book, and it accurately describes the subject matter.
Jeavons teaches you numerous methods to get a larger yield ins smatter
amount of apace, and with teas work, as well. An excellent book, whether
you're planting a small garden on the balcony of your apartment, or a large
plot to feed dozens of people.</P>

